libsahtrace: skip zone-level lookup above max effective level

sahTracevZ() resolves the per-zone trace level on every compiled zone trace,
before sahTraceOutput() decides whether to emit anything. Built with
SAHTRACES_LEVEL=500, the hot SAH_TRACEZ_INFO (400) and SAH_TRACEZ_IN/OUT (500)
call sites in tight loops - e.g. pwhm / libswla nl80211 station polling - each
pay a linear walk of the trace-zone list plus a strcmp per entry, and a second
walk for the "all" fallback, only for the result to be discarded. On a 114
station scaling run this zone-lookup subtree is ~5.9% of wld CPU.

For any name, sahTraceGetZoneLevel() returns a named zone level, the "all"
fallback level, or -1 - never more than the maximum level across all registered
zones. Track that maximum (maxEffectiveZoneLevel, -1 when no zones) and return
early from sahTracevZ() when the message level exceeds it: the trace could not
be output regardless of which zone resolves. This is one integer compare, no
allocation, output is byte-for-byte identical, and it degrades to the original
behaviour (a no-op guard) when a zone is genuinely enabled high.

The maximum is recomputed by walking the zone list at the four mutation points
that can change an effective level: sahTraceAddZone(), sahTraceRemoveZone(),
sahTraceRemoveAllZones() and sahTraceZoneSetLevel(). Recompute-all avoids the
stale-maximum bug an incremental update would hit when the current-max zone is
removed or lowered. Zone mutation is already documented as not thread safe, so
no locking is added; the integer is read locklessly on the hot path, matching
the existing zone-list contract.

Upstream-Status: Pending
Signed-off-by: Petr Štetiar <petr.stetiar@prplfoundation.org>
---
--- a/src/sahtrace.c
+++ b/src/sahtrace.c
@@ -116,6 +116,36 @@
 static sah_trace_zone* zones = NULL;
 struct timespec startTime = {0, 0};
 
+/*
+ * Highest effective trace level across all registered zones, or -1 when none
+ * are registered. For any name, sahTraceGetZoneLevel() returns either a named
+ * zone level, the "all" fallback level, or -1 - never more than this maximum.
+ * So sahTracevZ() can skip the zone-list walk entirely whenever the message
+ * level exceeds it (the trace could not be output anyway). Recomputed by
+ * sahTraceRecomputeMaxLevel() at every zone mutation. Like the rest of the zone
+ * state, this is not thread safe; zones must be mutated single threaded.
+ */
+static int maxEffectiveZoneLevel = -1;
+
+static void sahTraceRecomputeMaxLevel(void) {
+    sah_trace_zone* curZone = zones;
+    int m = -1;
+
+    while(curZone) {
+        /*
+         * Compare as signed int: sah_trace_level is an enum the compiler may
+         * give an unsigned underlying type, which would promote the m == -1
+         * sentinel to UINT_MAX and make the comparison always false.
+         */
+        int level = (int) curZone->level;
+        if(level > m) {
+            m = level;
+        }
+        curZone = curZone->next;
+    }
+    maxEffectiveZoneLevel = m;
+}
+
 
 /* function prototypes */
 static void sahTraceOutput(int lvl, int traceLvl, const char* format, va_list vl);
@@ -599,6 +629,7 @@
         zones = newZone;
     }
     newZone->level = lvl;
+    sahTraceRecomputeMaxLevel();
 }
 
 /**
@@ -625,6 +656,7 @@
             }
             free(curZone->name);
             free(curZone);
+            sahTraceRecomputeMaxLevel();
             return;
         }
         prevZone = curZone;
@@ -649,6 +681,7 @@
         free(zones);
         zones = curZone;
     }
+    sahTraceRecomputeMaxLevel();
 }
 
 /**
@@ -772,6 +805,7 @@
     }
 
     zone->level = lvl;
+    sahTraceRecomputeMaxLevel();
 }
 
 /**
@@ -859,6 +893,14 @@
    @param ap variable argument list
  */
 void sahTracevZ(int lvl, const char* zone, const char* format, va_list ap) {
+    /*
+     * Skip the zone-list walk when the message cannot be output for any zone.
+     * maxEffectiveZoneLevel bounds sahTraceGetZoneLevel() from above, so
+     * lvl > maxEffectiveZoneLevel proves sahTraceOutput() would discard it.
+     */
+    if(lvl > maxEffectiveZoneLevel) {
+        return;
+    }
     sahTraceOutput(lvl, sahTraceGetZoneLevel(zone), format, ap);
 }
 
